name: agent_mu_zig15_demo
version: "8.12.0"
language: zig
module: agent_mu_demo

description: |
  AGENT MU — Zig 0.15.1 Idioms Demo
  μ = 1/φ²/10 = 0.0382 — священная мутация

  Демонстрация того, как AGENT MU фиксит код:
  1. V01 — detect error
  2. Pi03 — classify (FixType)
  3. Phi02 — search pattern
  4. Mu05 — apply fix
  5. Sigma07 — log success

types:
  # Before/After pair for showing code transformation
  CodeExample:
    fields:
      idiom_name: String
      description: String
      before_code: String
      after_code: String
      compilation_error: String
      fix_type: String

  # AGENT MU fix result
  FixResult:
    fields:
      phase: String  # V01, Pi03, Phi02, Mu05, Sigma07
      success: Bool
      fix_type: String
      lines_changed: Int
      description: String

behaviors:
  - name: idiom1_comptime_generics
    given: Zig code with old comptime generic syntax
    when: Code uses GenericList(comptime Child: type)
    then:
      - Transform to List(comptime T: type)
      - Use @This() for self-reference
      - Add allocator-aware init function

  - name: idiom2_unmanaged_containers
    given: ArrayList.init(allocator) deprecated call
    when: Zig 0.15.1 compiler warns about ArrayList.init
    then:
      - Replace with ArrayListUnmanaged
      - Add allocator parameter to append()
      - Change deinit() to deinit(allocator)

  - name: idiom3_inferred_error_sets
    given: Explicit error set definition
    when: Function has simple error returns
    then:
      - Remove explicit error set
      - Use !T for inferred error union
      - Let compiler infer from body

  - name: idiom4_build_zig_modules
    given: Old b.addExecutable() with root_source_file
    when: Using Zig 0.15.1 build system
    then:
      - Use b.createModule() for module definition
      - Use .root_module in executable
      - Configure .imports for dependencies

  - name: idiom5_raygui_glassmorphism
    given: Basic rectangle drawing
    when: Rendering UI elements
    then:
      - Add glow layer with transparency
      - Draw glass background with rgba
      - Add neon border with DrawRectangleRoundedLines

  - name: idiom6_sacred_math_comptime
    given: Math calculations for phi, golden ratio
    when: Computing sacred constants
    then:
      - Use comptime for compile-time evaluation
      - Calculate phi = (1 + @sqrt(5.0)) / 2.0
      - Verify golden_identity = phi² + 1/phi² = 3.0

  - name: idiom7_inline_unrolling
    given: Performance-critical loops
    when: Loop body is small and fixed-size
    then:
      - Use inline for (0..N)
      - Add @setEvalBranchQuota if needed
      - Compiler unrolls at comptime

  - name: demonstrate_agent_mu_flow
    given: Generated code with Zig 0.15 errors
    when: Running AGENT MU verification
    then:
      - Show V01: zig build detects error
      - Show Pi03: diagnostic classifies fix type
      - Show Phi02: pattern matcher finds solution
      - Show Mu05: fixer applies transformation
      - Show Sigma07: logger records success

quality_gates:
  - name: gate_code_quality
    description: All generated code must compile with Zig 0.15.1
    acceptance:
      - zig build-obj passes
      - zig fmt --check passes
      - All 7 idioms demonstrated

  - name: gate_agent_mu_flow
    description: AGENT MU phases must be clearly shown
    acceptance:
      - V01 → Pi03 → Phi02 → Mu05 → Sigma07 flow demonstrated
      - Before/after examples for each idiom
      - FixType classification shown

config:
  show_before_after: true
  show_agent_mu_phases: true
  include_sacred_math: true
